uage Models\n10 None 2025 None MONICA: Real-Time Monitoring and Calibration of Chain-of-Thought Sycophancy in Large Reasoning Model\n11 None 2025 None SCSF: A Self-Checking and Selection Framework for Machine Translation based on Large Language Models\n12 None 2026 None ReBeCA: Unveiling Interpretable Behavior Hierarchy behind the Iterative Self-Reflection of Language \n13 None 2025 None When Meaning Stays the Same, but Models Drift: Evaluating Quality of Service under Token-Level Behav\n14 None 2019 None Representation Degeneration Problem in Training Natural Language Generation Models\n15 None 2021 None Too Much in Common: Shifting of Embeddings in Transformer Language Models and its Implications\nfields ['abstract', 'authors', 'citations', 'relevance', 'title', 'url', 'year']\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
