{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_47","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\nThis folder stores PDFs for the project **Representation Drift Under Self-Reflection**.\n\n## Primary papers downloaded (12)\n\n1. [Self-Refine: Iterative Refinement with Self-Feedback](2303.17651_Self-Refine_Iterative_Refinement_with_Self-Feedback.pdf)\n   - Authors: Aman Madaan et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - Source: arXiv:2303.17651\n   - Why relevant: canonical self-feedback refinement loop baseline.\n\n2. [Reflexion: Language Agents with Verbal Reinforcement Learning](2303.11366_Reflexion_Language_Agents_with_Verbal_Reinforcement_Learning.pdf)\n   - Authors: Noah Shinn et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - Source: arXiv:2303.11366\n   - Why relevant: strong iterative reflection baseline for reasoning agents.\n\n3. [CRITIC: Large Language Models Can Self-Correct with Tool-Interactive Critiquing](2305.11738_CRITIC_Tool-Interactive_Critiquing.pdf)\n   - Authors: Zhibin Gou et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - Source: arXiv:2305.11738\n   - Why relevant: tests self-correction with external verification, useful contrast to intrinsic reflection.\n\n4. [Large Language Models Cannot Self-Correct Reasoning Yet](2310.01798_Large_Language_Models_Cannot_Self-Correct_Reasoning_Yet.pdf)\n   - Authors: Jie Huang et al.\n   - Year: 2023 (ICLR 2024)\n   - Source: arXiv:2310.01798\n   - Why relevant: central evidence on intrinsic self-correction limits.\n\n5. [LLMs cannot find reasoning errors, but can correct them given the error location](acl2024-findings-826_LLMs_cannot_find_reasoning_errors_but_can_correct_them_given_error_location.pdf)\n   - Authors: Shengmin Jin et al.\n   - Year: 2024\n   - Source: Findings ACL 2024\n   - Why relevant: separates error localization from correction ability.\n\n6. [Large Language Models have Intrinsic Self-Correction Ability](2406.15673_Large_Language_Models_have_Intrinsic_Self-Correction_Ability.pdf)\n   - Authors: Dancheng Liu et al.\n   - Year: 2024\n   - Source: arXiv:2406.15673\n   - Why relevant: argues intrinsic correction exists under specific prompting/temperature settings.\n\n7. [Analysing the Residual Stream of Language Models Under Knowledge Conflicts](2410.16090_Analysing_the_Residual_Stream_of_Language_Models_Under_Knowledge_Conflicts.pdf)\n   - Authors: Yu Zhao et al.\n   - Year: 2024\n   - Source: arXiv:2410.16090\n   - Why relevant: directly probes residual-stream dynamics and conflict signals.\n\n8. [Inspecting and Editing Knowledge Representations in Language Models](2304.00740_Measuring_and_Manipulating_Knowledge_Representations_in_Language_Models.pdf)\n   - Authors: Evan Hernandez, Belinda Z. Li, Jacob Andreas\n   - Year: 2023 (COLM 2024)\n   - Source: arXiv:2304.00740\n   - Why relevant: linear probes and hidden-state interventions for knowledge.\n\n9. [Representation Engineering: A Top-Down Approach to AI Transparency](2310.01405_Representation_Engineering_A_Top-Down_Approach_to_AI_Transparency.pdf)\n   - Authors: Andy Zou et al.\n   - Year: 2023\n   - Source: arXiv:2310.01405\n   - Why relevant: representation-centric monitoring/control methods applicable to drift analysis.\n\n10. [Steering Language Models With Activation Engineering](2308.10248_Activation_Addition_Steering_Language_Models_Without_Optimization.pdf)\n    - Authors: Alexander Matt Turner et al.\n    - Year: 2023\n    - Source: arXiv:2308.10248\n    - Why relevant: activation-space interventions and direction vectors.\n\n11. [Refusal in Language Models Is Mediated by a Single Direction](2406.11717_Refusal_in_Language_Models_Is_Mediated_by_a_Single_Direction.pdf)\n    - Authors: Andy Arditi et al.\n    - Year: 2024\n    - Source: arXiv:2406.11717\n    - Why relevant: evidence of low-dimensional control directions in residual stream.\n\n12. [Understanding Reasoning in Thinking Language Models via Steering Vectors](2506.18167_Understanding_Reasoning_in_Thinking_Language_Models_via_Steering_Vectors.pdf)\n    - Authors: Constantin Venhoff et al.\n    - Year: 2025\n    - Source: arXiv:2506.18167\n    - Why relevant: links reasoning behaviors to steerable representation directions.\n\n## Paper-finder top hits that could not be fully downloaded\n\n- The Mirror Loop: Recursive Non-Convergence in Generative Reasoning Systems\n  - Semantic Scholar CorpusId:282388663 had no open-access PDF via API at retrieval time.\n- Learning from All: Concept Alignment for Autonomous Distillation from Multiple Drifting MLLMs\n  - Semantic Scholar API request was rate-limited (HTTP 429) during retrieval window.\n\n## Deep-reading chunk artifacts\n\nChunked PDFs for full-pass review of key papers are in \"'`papers/pages/`:\n- `2310.01798_...`\n- `2406.15673_...`\n- `2410.16090_...`\n\nRaw extraction notes from all chunks:\n- `papers/deep_reading_notes_raw.txt`\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/.gitignore << '\"'EOF'\n# Exclude all data files (can be large)\n*\n\n# Keep documentation and small samples\n\"'!.gitignore\n!README.md\n!dataset_summary.json\n!**/README.md\n!**/samples/\n!**/samples/**\n!**/download.sh\n!**/download_instructions.txt\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/README.md << '\"'EOF'\n# Downloaded Datasets\n\nThis directory contains local benchmark datasets for self-reflection and representation-drift experiments. Data files are excluded from git via \"'`.gitignore`.\n\n## Dataset 1: gsm8k (main)\n\n### Overview\n- Source: HuggingFace `gsm8k` (`main` config)\n- Size: train 7,473; test 1,319\n- Format: HuggingFace DatasetDict saved to disk\n- Task: grade-school math reasoning (final answer correctness)\n- Splits: train, test\n- License: see dataset card on HuggingFace\n\n### Download Instructions\nUsing HuggingFace (recommended):\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\ndataset = load_dataset(\"gsm8k\", \"main\")\ndataset.save_to_disk(\"datasets/gsm8k\")\n```\n\n### Loading\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\ndataset = load_from_disk(\"datasets/gsm8k\")\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- `datasets/gsm8k/samples/samples.json`\n\n## Dataset 2: commonsense_qa\n\n### Overview\n- Source: HuggingFace `commonsense_qa`\n- Size: train 9,741; validation 1,221; test 1,140\n- Format: HuggingFace DatasetDict saved to disk\n- Task: multiple-choice commonsense reasoning\n- Splits: train, validation, test\n- License: see dataset card on HuggingFace\n\n### Download Instructions\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\ndataset = load_dataset(\"commonsense_qa\")\ndataset.save_to_disk(\"datasets/commonsense_qa\")\n```\n\n### Loading\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\ndataset = load_from_disk(\"datasets/commonsense_qa\")\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- `datasets/commonsense_qa/samples/samples.json`\n\n## Dataset 3: truthful_qa (multiple_choice)\n\n### Overview\n- Source: HuggingFace `truthful_qa` (`multiple_choice` config)\n- Size: validation 817\n- Format: HuggingFace DatasetDict saved to disk\n- Task: truthfulness and misconception robustness\n- Splits: validation\n- License: see dataset card on HuggingFace\n\n### Download Instructions\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\ndataset = load_dataset(\"truthful_qa\", \"multiple_choice\")\ndataset.save_to_disk(\"datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice\")\n```\n\n### Loading\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\ndataset = load_from_disk(\"datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice\")\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- `datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice/samples/samples.json`\n\n## Notes\n- Dataset summary file: `datasets/dataset_summary.json`\n- These tasks support accuracy-style scoring and iterative self-critique evaluation loops.\nEOF\n\ncat > code/README.md << '\"'EOF'\n# Cloned Repositories\n\n## 1) self-refine\n- URL: https://github.com/madaan/self-refine\n- Purpose: Iterative self-feedback and refinement framework.\n- Location: \"'`code/self-refine/`\n- Key files:\n  - `src/gsm/run.py`\n  - `src/*/run.py` task pipelines\n- Notes:\n  - Requires LLM API setup.\n  - Includes GSM8K and other task examples for iterative refinement.\n\n## 2) reflexion\n- URL: https://github.com/noahshinn/reflexion\n- Purpose: Reflexion agents with verbal RL memory.\n- Location: `code/reflexion/`\n- Key files:\n  - `hotpotqa_runs/`\n  - `alfworld_runs/`\n  - `programming_runs/`\n- Notes:\n  - Uses OpenAI API key and environment-specific dependencies.\n  - Good baseline for multi-round reflection trajectories.\n\n## 3) representation-engineering\n- URL: https://github.com/andyzoujm/representation-engineering\n- Purpose: RepE/RepReading/RepControl for representation-level analysis and steering.\n- Location: `code/representation-engineering/`\n- Key files:\n  - `repe/`\n  - `examples/`\n  - `repe_eval/`\n- Notes:\n  - Strong fit for probing/steering residual-space directions.\n  - Install via `pip install -e .` in repo.\n\n## 4) activation_additions\n- URL: https://github.com/montemac/activation_additions\n- Purpose: Activation-vector injection and algebraic value editing.\n- Location: `code/activation_additions/`\n- Key files:\n  - `scripts/basic_functionality.py`\n  - `activation_additions/`\n- Notes:\n  - Uses hooks into residual stream (TransformerLens style).\n  - Useful for direction-based intervention baselines.\n\n## 5) llm-attacks\n- URL: https://github.com/llm-attacks/llm-attacks\n- Purpose: Optimization-based activation/prompt attack infrastructure.\n- Location: `code/llm-attacks/`\n- Key files:\n  - `experiments/`\n  - `llm_attacks/`\n- Notes:\n  - Not a direct reflection baseline, but useful for stress-testing robustness under perturbation.\n  - Typically expects high-memory GPUs and local model weights.\n\n## Validation status\n- Repositories cloned successfully.\n- Deep run tests were not executed due API/GPU/runtime requirements.\n- For experiment runner: start with `representation-engineering`, `activation_additions`, and `self-refine`.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
